HEADWORD: Euxanthic
<hw>Eux*an"thic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Having a yellow color; pertaining to, derived from, or resembling,
euxanthin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Euxanthic acid</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>a
yellow, crystalline, organic acid, extracted from
euxanthin.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Euxanthin</ent>⟦br⟧
